About us

A global luxury group, Kering manages the development of a series of renowned Houses in Fashion, Leather Goods, Jewelry and Watches: Gucci, Saint Laurent, Bottega Veneta, Balenciaga, Alexander McQueen, Brioni, Boucheron, Pomellato, Dodo, Qeelin, Ulysse Nardin, Girard-Perregaux, as well as Kering Eyewear. Kering has a dynamic and diverse workforce of 35,000 employees worldwide and delivered a revenue of €13.7 billion in 2018 - making the Group a leading player in the luxury industry.

The E-Commerce & Marketplace Team of Kering Group is currently seeking English/French speaker E-Commerce Transversal Project Manager to join our dynamic team based in France, Paris.
Job Description
Your opportunity
You are reporting to the Head of E-Commerce & Marketplace and are in charge of cross-functional projects, you coordinate, and support E-Commerce/Omnichannel Product Business Leads and you are accountable of project methodology and final delivery.
How you will contribute
Leading cross-functional projects, you are to define and drive project methodology and key deliverables;
Coordination of multiple stakeholders:
Building adhoc project organization, methodology and processes depending on challenges and involved stakeholders;
Organizing & leading workshops with key stakeholders;
Working closely with Product Leads (Frontend & UX, Checkout & Fulfilment, Marketplaces, Product Lifecycle) and Kering Technologies stakeholders (Architecture team, SI, software partners);
Defining business cases taking inputs from brands, Kering technologies, operations and other group functions;
Incorporating market insights and best practices.
Accountable of the quality of deliverables and final delivery:
Project budget & planning follow-up;
Processes definition;
Requirements documentation and translation in project tools: Jira, Confluence;
Delivery plan.
Who you are
A Business or Engineer graduate Master in Digital is a plus;
A Digital, Ecommerce, Omnichannel expert with at least 6-8 years of experience;
Experience of Agile methodology on cross-functional projects;
Strong rapport with solution engineers and a deep understanding of the end-to-end development lifecycle;
Knowledge of e-commerce and omnichannel, you have an extensive understanding of key components of an e-commerce platform: payment, fraud, UX, order management;
Advanced usage of project management tools: Jira, Confluence, Slack;
A professional with strong analytical, ownership and accountability skills;
You’ve experienced retail & omnichannel environments in an international context, ideally in the luxury industry;
An excellent communicator at every level in the organization with excellent interpersonal skills;
Fluent in English, both written and spoken.
Why work with us?
This is an excellent opportunity to join the Kering adventure in a moment of extraordinary growth and become part of a dynamic team in a global Luxury group that offers endless possibilities to learn and grow. Talent development is a managerial principle at Kering and we are committed to fostering internal mobility. Our common vision promotes leadership skills and helps every employee to reach their full potential in a stimulating and fulfilling workplace environment. Kering is committed to building a diverse workforce. We believe diversity in all its forms – gender, age, nationality, culture, religious beliefs and sexual orientation – enriches the workplace. It opens up opportunities for people to express their talent, both individually and collectively and it helps foster our ability to adapt to a changing world. As an Equal Opportunity Employer, we welcome and consider applications from all qualified candidates, regardless of their background.
